100
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,200
Criminal Law Article 158.

101
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,000
Do you know it?

102
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,600
Article 159.

103
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,240
Do you know what it says?

104
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,200
Yes, I know all of it.

105
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,840
Criminal Law Article 158.

106
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,320
Yes, theoretically,

107
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,000
you can

108
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,120
detain him for another month.

109
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:55,840
Article 159,

110
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:56,600
on top of that,

111
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,120
you can further

112
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,560
extend detention for another month.

113
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:58,960
The problem is,

114
00:04:58,960 --> 00:04:59,600
you don't have

115
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,200
any key witnesses or evidence.

116
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,360
Because he didn't kill anyone.

117
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,760
So how can you convict him?

118
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,480
That's exactly why we can't convict him,

119
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,360
so we're still detaining him.

120
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,240
It's because of insufficient evidence

121
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,960
that the prosecutor's office

122
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:12,000
